question:
Suppose that $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}  
-2  & -1 & 1 \\ 
0 & 1 & 2\\
2  & 1 & -2\end{array}
\right)$, $B=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}  
4  & 1 & 0\end{array}
\right)$, and $C=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}  
0  & 3 & -1\end{array}
\right)$. Find $X$ if $X\cdot A-B=C$.

Let $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
-1 & 2 & 1 \\ 
7 & 1 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$,  $B=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-1 & 1 \\ 
7 & 1 \\ 
2 & 0 \end{array}
\right),$ and $C=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-1 & 2 \\ 
0 & 1 \end{array}
\right)$. Which of the following statements is correct?

Consider the following statements: 
S1:  If $A$ is a $4 \times 4$ matrix such that $\mathrm{det}=-2$, then $\mathrm{det} \left( 2 A^T A^{-1} \right)=16$; 
S2: Let $A$ be an $m \times n$ matrix. If the equation $A\textbf{x}=\textbf{0}$ has only the trivial solution $x \in \mathbb{R}^n$, then the columns of $A$ are linearly independent.

Find $a$ such that the matrix $\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2 & 3 \\ 
4 & 5 & 6 \\ 
3 & 2 & a \end{array}
\right)$ is singular.

Find the rank of the matrix  $\left( \begin{array}{rrr}  
-1  & z & 2 \\ 
1 & -1 & 1\\
z  & -1 & 1\end{array}
\right)$, where $z$ is a real number.

Find $x$ and $y$ such that $\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-2 & 1 \\ 
3 & -4 \end{array}
\right)\left( \begin{array}{rr}
x & 2 \\ 
1 & y \end{array}
\right)=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-3 & 1 \\ 
2 & -14 \end{array}
\right)$.

Suppose that $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
2 & 0 & -1 \\ 
3 & 1 & 0 \\ 
-2 & 1 & 3 \end{array}
\right)$.

Find matrix $B$ such that matrices $A$ and $B$ are inverses.

Find the real values of $m$ for which the following set of vectors $V=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
1\\ 
2 \\
m \end{array}
\right)$, $Z=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
1\\ 
-1 \\
m \end{array}
\right)$, and
$W=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
3\\ 
m+2 \\
1 \end{array}
\right)$ is linearly independent.

Suppose that $$A=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2  & -1  \\ 
0 & 0 & 2  \\ 
-1 & -2 & 3  \\ 
2 & 4 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$$ and $$B=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
0 & 1  & 1  \\ 
2 & 2 & 0  \\ 
0 & 3 & 2 \end{array}
\right).$$ Which of the following matrices has rank $3$?

Let  $A=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
1 & 3 \\ 
2 & -1 \end{array}
\right)$ and $f\left(x\right)=x^3-2x+5I_{2\times2}$. Find $f(A)$.
